result.formatted_address: 3 Ngan Wan Road, Mui Wo, Hong Kong
result.name: China Bear

reviews.text: So upgraded my opinion here. Food is good, price point is perhaps better than other restaurants on Lantau vis-a-vis value for money. And even though it's on a dock, you get to look out at the sea. Would return.
This is a great bar in Mui Wo. The staff are friendly. It is right by the water with a great atmosphere

Great location right next to the ocean, al fresco dining and drinking very relaxing. Pork stuffed squid is excellent and highly recommended. 

Most waitresses - with one prominent exception  - very friendly and outgoing. 

They've recently reintroduced the 'Sunday Roast'  complete with Yorkshire pudding. The meat was a bit cold and tough, but I'm looking forward to the beef.

Bring cash - they don't take credit cards.
Great place to have a beer and wait for ferries
Friendly staff, yummy food, great outdoor seats
